title: Belfry drops to No. 4 in Mountain Top 10, Southwestern jumps up a spot
text:
/ Headlines List / Article 
HAZARD, Ky. (WYMT) -- The (3A) Belfry Pirates struggled to defeat (3A) Lawrence County and have moved down a spot for the second week in a row. 
Meanwhile, (5A) Southwestern jumps the Pirates, as the Warriors have reeled off five straight wins. 
The Associated Press has Pulaski County rated as the No. 3 team in the entire state in class 5A behind Bowling Green and Owensboro; the Maroons are No. 1 in the Mountain Top 10. 
MOUNTAIN TOP 10 (After Week 7) 
1. Pulaski County (30)2. Johnson Central (25) (26)3. Southwestern (25)5. North Laurel (15) (16)6. Bell County (14) (15)7. Paintsville (14)
